<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-039-314 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 361 953</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Oct 7 1991 v8 n40 p17(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Intellicom eyes aggressively priced local Ethernet bridge. (plansto introduce QuickNet 6000) (brief article) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Musich, Paula.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Intellicom Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Intellicom Quick-Net 6000 (Bridge device) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionBridges (Connector).andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Paula MusichandM;Vying for the title of &quot;commodity king&quot; in the Ethernet bridge market,Intellicom plans to announce at Comdex/Fall this month a new local bridgethat company officials say costs 48 percent to 60 percent less than similarproducts.andM;The Chatsworth, Calif., firm will offer its Quick-Net 6000, which bridgeslocal Ethernet networks, for $1,975, officials said.andP;  A similarly equippedlocal bridge from Retix, by comparison, costs $2,650.andM;The average price of a local bridge is $3,600, according to a spokespersonfor market researcher Dataquest Inc. in San Jose, Calif.andM;&quot;That's an aggressive price,&quot; said Susan Frankle, a senior analyst atmarket-research firm International Data Corp. in Framingham, Mass.andP;  &quot;LocalEthernet bridging is going to become very commoditylike.&quot;andM;The Quick-Net 6000 media access control-layer bridge implements the mostrecent version of the spanning tree bridging standard.andP;  It also includes aSimple Network Management Protocol agent that allows the bridge to be managedby any vendor's SNMP manager, as well as two thick-Ethernet and twothin-Ethernet connections.andP;  A $99 transceiver supporting 10BaseT connectionsis also offered.andM;The Quick-Com 6000 bridge will be available 30 days after receipt of orderfrom OEMs and resellers.andP;  A non-managed version of the bridge will also beavailable for $1,475.andO;</TEXT></DOC>